    • Method Detail

      • getCloseTicketConfirmationMessage

        public static java.lang.String getCloseTicketConfirmationMessage(TroubleTicket troubleTicket)
        Helper method used by the UI to display an appropriate message when the user tries to close a trouble ticket. Will either be something like "Are you sure you want to close this trouble ticket?" or "There are open activities on this trouble ticket. If you close the ticket, the activities will also be closed. Are you sure you want to close this trouble ticket?"
        Parameters:
        troubleTicket - the trouble ticket
        Returns:
        an appropriate confirmation message for closing the given trouble ticket

      • getRelatedEntityDisplayName

        public static java.lang.String getRelatedEntityDisplayName(Bean relatedEntity)
        Helper method use by the UI to display a user-readable name for the related entity. For most related entities this simply results in a call to getDisplayName on the entity. But for a Policy it is a bit more complicated because the Policy itself is just a container of PolicyPeriods, and so in that situation we grab the display name from one of the PolicyPeriods
        Parameters:
        relatedEntity - (an Account, PolicyPeriod, or Producer that is related to the trouble ticket)
        Returns:
        user readable display name for the related entity

      • getRelatedEntityTypeDisplayName

        public static java.lang.String getRelatedEntityTypeDisplayName(Bean relatedEntity)
        Helper method used by the UI so we can display a user-readable name for the type of an entity related to the trouble ticket. For example, in a list view that displays the entities related to a trouble ticket, one column might display the type of each entity and this method will return a user readable name for that type (for example: "Account" or "Producer" or "PolicyPeriod")
        Parameters:
        relatedEntity - (an Account, PolicyPeriod, or Producer that is related to the trouble ticket)
        Returns:
        user readable display name for the type of an entity that is related to a trouble ticket
